==English==

===Etymology===
The heads of some battering rams were carved in the shape of a '''[[ram]]''', an animal renowned for [[butt]]ing with its head.

===Noun===
'''[[battering]] [[ram]]''' (''plural'' '''[[battering rams]]''')
#(''also'' '''ram''') A heavy object used for [[batter]]ing down [[wall]]s before [[gunpowder]] was known in [[Europe]].
# {{heraldry}} This object borne as a [[charge]] in a [[coat of arms]].

